      <memberdef kind="variable" id="namespacebindless_1a75caf9db16efa8e0a355f91750d826f4" prot="public" static="no" constexpr="yes" mutable="no">
        <type>constexpr uint32_t</type>
        <definition>constexpr uint32_t bindless::MAX_RESOURCE_INDEX_BITS</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>MAX_RESOURCE_INDEX_BITS</name>
        <qualifiedname>bindless::MAX_RESOURCE_INDEX_BITS</qualifiedname>
        <initializer>= 16u</initializer>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>DX12 has a limit of 1000000 and similarly as with samplers, we need some space for descriptors that are not bindless. Right now the limit is somewhat arbitrary chosen to be 65K, we probably need far less than that, but this gives us lot of bindless room to work with. This limit also allows bit packing to be used, to reduce memory usage. A sampler and texture bindless index can be packed into one 32 bit int with some extra bits for extra info. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
